aped slaves, military-civilian competition in the launch program, and international intrigue. Throughout, he illuminates Brazil's changing politics of inequality and examines how such inequality is made, reproduced, and challenged. How people conceptualize and act on the unequal conditions in which they find themselves, he shows, is as much a cultural and historical matter as a material one. Deftly broadening our understanding of race, technology, development, and political consciousness on local, national, and global levels, Constellations of Inequality paints a portrait of contemporary Brazil that will interest a broad spectrum of readers.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aBlacksxLand tenurezBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEconomic development projectsxPolitical aspectszBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEqualityzBrazilzAlcântara. 0aEqualityzBrazilzAlcântara. 0aLaunch complexes (Astronautics)zBrazilzAlcântara. 0aQuilomboszBrazilzAlcântaraxGovernment relations. 4aBrazil. 4aBrazilian Space Program. 4aConsciousness. 4aEthnography. 4aInequality. 4aPolitics. 4aQuilombolas. 4aRace. 4aTechnoscience. 4aUtopia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226499437423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226499437.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-063851-6  DG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019c2016d2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles